    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_3]",
      "span_text": "In the case of O2, it has been found by calculations in quartz and berlinite that there is no significant accuracy loss by equalizing the oxygens in Si-O-Si and Al-O-P.  Also, employing O2 in Si-O2-Al where O2 is not holding a proton (neighbour to Brønsted site) was found a reasonable approximation and, more importantly, introduced a considerable simplicity in a model that would have become complex if too many oxygen types had to be assigned for each system."
